# Enforce LF line endings on all text files. Without this, mixed
# Windows/macOS/Linux dev machines bounce CRLF↔LF on every save and
# pollute review diffs with thousands of "EOL-only" line changes.
#
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` forces
# LF on checkout AND in the index. `core.autocrlf` is a per-machine
# setting that disagrees across the team — a repo-level
# `.gitattributes` is the only way to make this stick.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Lockfiles + JSON: explicitly text + LF so tooling-rewritten files
# don't drift when editors / lints touch them.
*.json text eol=lf
*.lock text eol=lf
package-lock.json text eol=lf

# Treat known-binary so git doesn't try to normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
